.TH "ti_bandgap_writel" 9 "ti_bandgap_writel" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ti_bandgap_writel \- simple write helper function
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ti_bandgap_writel
.BI "(struct ti_bandgap *bgp "  ","
.BI "u32 val "  ","
.BI "u32 reg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bgp" 12
pointer to ti_bandgap structure
.IP "val" 12
desired register value to be written
.IP "reg" 12
desired register (offset) to be written
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Helper function to write bandgap registers. It uses the io remapped area.
